{"id": "duc04-testb-16:0#2", "contents": "Several individuals, including Dr. Rymer and Dr. Stanley Turecki, a child and family psychiatrist in New York, have expressed outrage at these solicitations. Dr. Turecki described the calls as \"consumer fraud,\" while Dr. Rymer stated that she was \"incensed.\" Kenneth Gross, a Washington lawyer specializing in election law, noted that while the practice may not be illegal, it is a \"fund-raising gimmick to get attention.\" Fred Wertheimer, president of Democracy 21, a nonprofit advocate of campaign finance reform, criticized the practice as \"buyer be damned\" and argued that Congress would investigate similar tactics if they were used by businesses."}
